Ext.data.JsonP['JSONPath']({"guide":"<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\" ?>\n<!DOCTYPE html PUBLIC \"-//W3C//DTD XHTML 1.0 Transitional//EN\"\n        \"http://www.w3.org/TR/xhtml1/DTD/xhtml1-transitional.dtd\">\n<html xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\">\n<head>\n    <title>JSONPath</title>\n\n    <meta http-equiv=\"Content-Type\" content=\"text/html; charset=UTF-8\">\n    <meta content=\"Scroll EclipseHelp Exporter\" name=\"generator\">\n\n    <link type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n    <link type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\">\n    <link type=\"text/css\" rel=\"stylesheet\" media=\"print\">\n</link></link></link></meta></meta></head>\n<body>\n    <div class=\"container\">\n\t\t<div id=\"banner\" class=\"confbox admonition admonition-note aui-message warning shadowed information-macro\">\n\t\t\t<p>You can now find Appcelerator documentation at <a href=\"https://docs.axway.com/\" target=\"_blank\">https://docs.axway.com/</a>. This site will be taken down in the near future.</p>\n\t\t</div>\n        <div class=\"header\"/>\n\n        <div id=\"src-49158409\" class=\"content\">\n                        <h1>JSONPath</h1>\n    <p>JSONPath is referred to commonly throughout this documentation. It is a string that is used to query objects at a number of points within the flow. A query is run on a JSON object and will return an array of matches.    </p>\n    <p>More details can be found here: <a class=\"external-link external-link\" href=\"https://www.npmjs.com/package/jsonpath\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.npmjs.com/package/jsonpath</a>    </p>\n    <div class=\"section section-2 \" id=\"src-49158409_JSONPath-Queryexamples\">\n        <h2 class=\"heading \"><span>Query examples</span></h2>\n    <p>This example shows a potential object which could be queried by JSONPath. The following examples show a selector, and the object which would be resolved by the Flow when performing the query.    </p>\n    <div class=\"confbox programlisting defaultnew syntaxhighlighter scroll-html-formatted-code\">\n                <div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\" class=\"defaultnew syntaxhighlighter scroll-html-formatted-code\">\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"comments\">// object being queried</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"keyword\">var</code><code class=\"plain\"> object = {</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">foo: {</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">  bar: </code><code class=\"string\">&quot;baz&quot;</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\"> }</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">};</code></div>\n</div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"section section-3 \" id=\"src-49158409_JSONPath-Rootobject\">\n        <h3 class=\"heading \"><span>Root object</span></h3>\n    <p>Returns all matches for the value of the whole object.    </p>\n    <div class=\"confbox programlisting defaultnew syntaxhighlighter scroll-html-formatted-code\">\n                <div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\" class=\"defaultnew syntaxhighlighter scroll-html-formatted-code\">\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"string\">&quot;$&quot;</code><code class=\"plain\"> </code><code class=\"comments\">// [{foo: { bar: &quot;baz&quot;} }]</code></div>\n</div>\n    </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"section section-3 \" id=\"src-49158409_JSONPath-Property\">\n        <h3 class=\"heading \"><span>Property</span></h3>\n    <p>Returns all matches for the value of the property &#x201C;foo&#x201D; on the root object.    </p>\n    <div class=\"confbox programlisting defaultnew syntaxhighlighter scroll-html-formatted-code\">\n                <div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\" class=\"defaultnew syntaxhighlighter scroll-html-formatted-code\">\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"string\">&quot;$.foo&quot;</code><code class=\"plain\"> </code><code class=\"comments\">// [{ bar: &quot;baz&quot; }]</code></div>\n</div>\n    </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"section section-3 \" id=\"src-49158409_JSONPath-Nestedproperty\">\n        <h3 class=\"heading \"><span>Nested property</span></h3>\n    <p>Returns all matches for the value of <tt class=\" \">bar</tt> on the property <tt class=\" \">foo</tt> of the root object.    </p>\n    <div class=\"confbox programlisting defaultnew syntaxhighlighter scroll-html-formatted-code\">\n                <div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\" class=\"defaultnew syntaxhighlighter scroll-html-formatted-code\">\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"string\">&quot;$.foo.bar&quot;</code><code class=\"plain\"> </code><code class=\"comments\">// [&quot;baz&quot;]</code></div>\n</div>\n    </div>\n    </div>\n    <div class=\"section section-3 \" id=\"src-49158409_JSONPath-Non-existentproperty\">\n        <h3 class=\"heading \"><span>Non-existent property</span></h3>\n    <p>Returns all matches for the value of property <tt class=\" \">bar</tt> on the root object. The root object does not contain that property so nothing is matched.    </p>\n    <div class=\"confbox programlisting defaultnew syntaxhighlighter scroll-html-formatted-code\">\n                <div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\" class=\"defaultnew syntaxhighlighter scroll-html-formatted-code\">\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"string\">&quot;$.bar&quot;</code><code class=\"plain\"> </code><code class=\"comments\">// []</code></div>\n</div>\n    </div>\n    <p>In these examples only up to a single result is returned, however there are times when more complex selectors will be used, and multiple results are expected.    </p>\n    <p>In the majority of cases only a single value will be required. JSONPath in API Builder Flows supports an extension to the suffix of a query, allowing a value at a certain index to be selected from the array of matches. Almost all the time 0 will be the index, selecting the first value matched since only one was expected.    </p>\n    <div class=\"tablewrap\">\n        <table class=\"confluenceTable\">\n        <thead class=\" \">    <tr>\n            <td class=\"confluenceTh\" rowspan=\"1\" colspan=\"1\">\n        <p>JSONPath Selector    </p>\n            </td>\n                <td class=\"confluenceTh\" rowspan=\"1\" colspan=\"1\">\n        <p>Description    </p>\n            </td>\n        </tr>\n</thead><tfoot class=\" \"/><tbody class=\" \">    <tr>\n            <td class=\"confluenceTd\" rowspan=\"1\" colspan=\"1\">\n        <p><tt class=\" \">|</tt>    </p>\n            </td>\n                <td class=\"confluenceTd\" rowspan=\"1\" colspan=\"1\">\n        <p>Index operator    </p>\n            </td>\n        </tr>\n</tbody>        </table>\n            </div>\n    <div class=\"section section-4 \" id=\"src-49158409_JSONPath-Example\">\n        <h4 class=\"heading \"><span>Example</span></h4>\n    <p>This shows a potential object which could be queried by JSONPath. The following examples show a selector, and the object which would be resolved by the Flow when performing the query.    </p>\n    <div class=\"confbox programlisting defaultnew syntaxhighlighter scroll-html-formatted-code\">\n                <div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\" class=\"defaultnew syntaxhighlighter scroll-html-formatted-code\">\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"comments\">// object being queried</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"keyword\">var</code><code class=\"plain\"> object = {</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\"> foo: {</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">   bar: </code><code class=\"string\">&quot;baz&quot;</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\"> },</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\"> foo2: {</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">   qux: </code><code class=\"string\">&quot;quux&quot;</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\"> }</code></div>\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"plain\">};</code></div>\n</div>\n    </div>\n    <p>This example shows the first result of the query for the value of <tt class=\" \">foo.bar</tt>.    </p>\n    <div class=\"confbox programlisting defaultnew syntaxhighlighter scroll-html-formatted-code\">\n                <div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\" class=\"defaultnew syntaxhighlighter scroll-html-formatted-code\">\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"string\">&quot;$.foo.bar|0&quot;</code><code class=\"plain\"> </code><code class=\"comments\">// &quot;baz&quot;</code></div>\n</div>\n    </div>\n    <p>This example uses <tt class=\" \">*</tt> which selects all properties. This is being performed on the root object, so both the values of <tt class=\" \">foo</tt> and <tt class=\" \">foo2</tt> will be matched. The index operator is used to select the first match.    </p>\n    <div class=\"confbox programlisting defaultnew syntaxhighlighter scroll-html-formatted-code\">\n                <div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\" class=\"defaultnew syntaxhighlighter scroll-html-formatted-code\">\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"string\">&quot;$.*|0&quot;</code><code class=\"plain\"> </code><code class=\"comments\">// {bar: &quot;baz&quot;}</code></div>\n</div>\n    </div>\n    <p>Similarly in this case, the index operator is used to select the second match.    </p>\n    <div class=\"confbox programlisting defaultnew syntaxhighlighter scroll-html-formatted-code\">\n                <div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\" class=\"defaultnew syntaxhighlighter scroll-html-formatted-code\">\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"string\">&quot;$.*|1&quot;</code><code class=\"plain\"> </code><code class=\"comments\">// {qux: &quot;quux&quot;}</code></div>\n</div>\n    </div>\n    <p>In this case, <tt class=\" \">baz</tt> does not exist, so there was no match. Selecting an index of a non-matching selector will result in a value of undefined.    </p>\n    <div class=\"confbox programlisting defaultnew syntaxhighlighter scroll-html-formatted-code\">\n                <div xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml\" class=\"defaultnew syntaxhighlighter scroll-html-formatted-code\">\n<div class=\"line\"><code class=\"string\">&quot;$.baz|0&quot;</code><code class=\"plain\"> </code><code class=\"comments\">// undefined</code></div>\n</div>\n    </div>\n    </div>\n    </div>\n    </div>\n        </div><a id=\"editButton\" href=\"https://wiki.appcelerator.org/pages/editpage.action?pageId=49158409\"><span>Edit</span></a>\n    \n        \n    </div>\n</body>\n</html>\n","title":"JSONPath"});